<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUL 92 / France dashes Gatt hopes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR John Major's hopes of a breakthrough in the Uruguay Round of trade
liberalisation talks at this week's Munich summit foundered yesterday on
opposition from France.
Although G7 officials said differences had narrowed in the contentious area
of farm support, France's President Francois Mitterrand refused to sanction
progress, apparently for fear of losing support in September's referendum on
the Maastricht Treaty. Mr Major admitted that there was 'no chance of an
agreement being reached' in Munich. Report, Page 2
</TEXT>
