<TEXT>
Sir, Lex ('Leave it to the board', July 6) says that if shareholders do not
trust the directors they should not buy their shares.
Very true. In the case of the latest flotations the names of the directors
are not disclosed in their invitation to subscribe.
One cannot trust someone whose name, let alone whose antecedents, one does
not know.
