FT  07 JUL 92 / San Fermin bull-running festival opens in Pamplona
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Thousands of people celebrating the official opening of the San Fermin
bull-running festival in the centre of the northern Spanish town of Pamplona
yesterday. The main attractions of the nine-day festival are the daily
encierros (bull runs), starting today, when hundreds of Spaniards and
foreigners wind up all-night bouts of drinking and eating with a test of
bravery, charging ahead of bulls which are let loose to run through the
streets to the bull ring. Dozens of people are gored each year.
