   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
R. J. REYNOLDS Tobacco, part of the RJR Nabisco group, has formed a joint
venture company with Tabacalera, the Spanish government-owned cigarette
manufacturing company, to produce and market RJR's Camel and Winston brands
in Spain.
The two brands have been produced under licence by Tabacalera since the
early-1980s. However, RJR said that the joint venture company structure  -
which will be owned 50:50 by the two manufacturers - will aid co-operation
and help further growth.
RJR is contributing its manufacturing facility in La Palma in the Canary
Islands, to the joint venture, and Tabacalera is understood to be putting in
an unspecified cash element.
