after Renold said the approach was unwelcome. TT also holds a 39.9 per cent
stake in Magnetic Materials following last year's unsuccessful takeover bid.
TT is keen to expand the business of its Crystalate division, maker of
electronic components, and may be especially attracted by AB's resistor
networks.
TT expressed interest in some AB operations earlier this year, but the
discussions faltered. TT's latest approach was unexpected.
AB, which reported pre-tax losses of Pounds 3.95m in the six months to 31
December, has also been discussing the sale or restructuring of other
divisions
