<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 92 / Management (The Growing Business): Buying out of the company
 -In a Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Corporate divestments provided the source for an increased number of
management buy-outs in Europe last year, according to the 1992 edition of
Europe Buy-out Review.* Last year, 62 per cent of buy-outs were the result
of corporate restructuring compared with 53 per cent in 1990.
The number of buy-outs of private or family-owned businesses fell to 33 from
36 per cent of the total while 'other' sources accounted for 5 per cent (11
per cent). Only in France and Italy did private or family companies account
for more than half the buy-outs. The number of continental European buy-outs
fell from 411 in 1990 to 318 last year but there was a much smaller fall in
the value of completed deals: from Pounds 4bn to Pounds 3.9bn. This compared
with a UK market in 1991 of 564 deals with a total value of Pounds 2.8bn.
*Initiative Europe, 69-71 Bondway, London SW8 1SQ. Tel 071 735 9838. 180
pages. Pounds 255.
