<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 92 / Survey of Software at Work (25): Lloyds Bank - Company
Snapshot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Lloyds is one of the top four UK banks. Its income last year was Pounds
3.98bn and profit after tax was Pounds 449m. The bank has more than 71,700
staff, of whom 62,000 are in the UK.
The Corporate Banking and Treasury Unit includes banking services for
companies, leasing, and trade finance. It also includes Europe's biggest
share registration operation. The unit made an Pounds 11m pre-tax loss last
year.
It has 2,550 staff in the UK, New York and Tokyo.
