<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 92 / Survey of Software at Work (16): Travellog Systems -
Supplier Profile
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Travellog Systems was formed in 1983 and concentrates solely on reservation
systems for tour operators. It claims to be the market leader in systems for
ferry and motoring holidays.
Customers: Its 25 customers include the AA, French Life Holidays, the
Caravan Club, plus Sally Ferries, P&amp;O Scottish Ferries and Eurotunnel, which
has just signed for a system to handle its bookings.
Status: Travellog became a private limited company two years ago.
Financial Statistics: Turnover: Pounds 1.35m in 1991-92; Pounds 809,000 in
1990-91. Net profit: Pounds 81,000 in 1991-92; Pounds 34,000 in 1990-91.
Staff: 34 staff members spread between head office in Haywards Heath,
Sussex, and the sales office in Borehamwood, Hertfordshire.
