<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 92 / Survey of Software at Work (17): RAC Enterprises - Company
Snapshot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Company details: the RAC has 5.2m members and a turnover of Pounds 177m. Its
traditional rival, the AA, has 7m members but the RAC claims to be growing
more quickly.
RAC Enterprises: The holidays and travel services operation in Croydon,
south London, is part of RAC Enterprises, which has a turnover of Pounds
17m.
The business also includes information services, hotel inspection services,
vehicle and dealer inspection services and publishing.
The holiday services unit offers self-catering holidays in France, ferry and
Motorail booking services and international breakdown recovery services. It
has a reservations team of 15 which is increased by 13 seasonal staff for
the peak booking period.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
