<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 92 / Survey of Software at Work (12): Hambros Leasing - Company
Snapshot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE company was formed in 1983 as a subsidiary of merchant bank, Hambros
Bank. Hambros Leasing specialises in medium-sized leasing tickets of Pounds
1m or more, ranging from big computers to oil drilling rigs.
The company's 1990-91 income was Pounds 106.8m with pre-tax profit of Pounds
18.6m.
The cost of assets currently leased directly, or through operations managed
by other companies, is Pounds 1.2bn. The company has 3,000 leases
outstanding and 36 staff.
