<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 92 / Survey of Software at Work (13): CHP Consulting - Supplier
Profile
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CHP Consulting is a UK company formed in May 1990 by three leasing computing
specialists from Andersen Consulting.
Financial details: turnover: Pounds 410,000 in first year, 1990-91;60 per
cent growth expected for 1991-92. Pre-tax profit: Pounds 255,000 in 1990-91.
Staff: ten, including the three founder directors, plus two part-time
support staff.
Services: computing consultancy and bespoke software development in the
leasing and asset finance industry, mainly on IBM AS/400 and System 38
computers.
